Global Stock Data Extractor — Multi-Country, 50-Year Daily Data
===============================================================
40 countries: USA, Germany, France, UK, Spain, Netherlands, Switzerland,
Sweden, Italy, Japan, Australia, Canada, Brazil, India, South Korea,
Hong Kong, Singapore, Denmark, Norway, Finland, Poland, South Africa,
Belgium, Portugal, Austria, Ireland, Mexico, New Zealand,
China (CSI300), Taiwan (TWSE50), Turkey (BIST30),
Indonesia (IDX30), Saudi Arabia (TASI),
Malaysia (KLCI30), Thailand (SET50), Israel (TA-35), Greece (ATHEX20),
Czech Republic (PX), Hungary (BUX), Argentina (MERVAL)

Fixes applied (X–XV):
  - update_cache: REPLACE not union-merge
  - Wikipedia scraper: HK zero-padding + SEHK prefix strip + per-country exclude
  - Belgium/Portugal/Finland corrected; China/Taiwan dtype bugs fixed
  - 9 new countries (XI–XIII): China, Taiwan, Turkey, Indonesia, Saudi Arabia,
    Malaysia, Thailand, Israel, Greece
  - 122 ticker additions from ticker_cache.json (XIV)
  - 4 error-reduction fixes (XV): SEHK cache poisoning, cross-country suffix
    bleed, Austria/Norway/Ireland exclude lists, SP500/Mexico suffix fixes

New countries (XVI):
  Czech Republic (.PR), Hungary (.BD), Argentina (.BA)

New error-reduction fixes (XVIII):
  Fix B — HTTP 404 instant retire (targets 259 errors/run):
    HTTP 404 responses are caught immediately in both rank_by_market_cap()
    and download_with_retry(). The ticker is retired to retired_tickers.json
    and the retry loop is skipped entirely. A 404 is a permanent failure —
    no retry will ever succeed.

  Fix C — Persistent failure counter (targets 1,761 errors/run):
    failure_counts.json tracks consecutive "no timezone" / "no price data"
    failures per ticker across separate runs. After FAIL_THRESHOLD=3
    consecutive failures a ticker is auto-retired. A single success resets
    the counter. Counters are updated after both the ranking phase and the
    download phase. Startup cleanup removes already-retired tickers from
    the counts file.

  Fix D — Post-download suffix validation (targets 8 entire-country failures):
    After yf.download() returns, column names are validated against the
    country's expected exchange suffix. Wrong-suffix columns (cross-country
    bleed) are dropped. If ALL columns are wrong, a per-ticker fallback
    download loop is triggered instead of skipping the country entirely.
    This eliminates the "No ranked tickers matched downloaded columns"
    catastrophic failure that caused whole countries to produce zero output.
  Output CSV now has 9 prefix columns before the ticker and price dates:
    Col A: Full company name  (from yfinance longName / shortName)
    Col B: Sector Code        (GICS 2-digit, e.g. 10)
    Col C: Sector             (e.g. Energy)
    Col D: Group Code         (GICS 4-digit, e.g. 1010)
    Col E: Industry Group     (e.g. Energy Equipment & Services)
    Col F: Industry Code      (GICS 6-digit, e.g. 101010)
    Col G: Industry           (e.g. Energy Equipment & Services)
    Col H: Sub-Industry Code  (GICS 8-digit, e.g. 10101010)
    Col I: Sub-Industry       (e.g. Oil & Gas Drilling)
    Col J: Ticker             (was Col A in XVI and earlier)
    Col K onwards: daily close prices (unchanged)
  The GICS hierarchy is resolved via a lookup file (GICS_Structure_2026.xlsx)
  placed next to the script. If the file is absent, columns B–I are left blank.

Run modes:
  python script.py                          # all 40 countries, sequential
  python script.py --group europe           # Europe only (20 countries)
  python script.py --group americas         # Americas only (5 countries)
  python script.py --group asia             # Asia-Pacific + MiddleEast + Africa (15)
  python script.py --country 'Czech Republic'
  python script.py --country Hungary
